==English==
=== Etymology ===
Latin ''[[uxorius]]'' "of or pertaining to a wife" from ''[[uxor]]'' "wife"

=== Adjective ===
'''uxorious'''
# overly [[devoted]] or [[submissive]] to one's [[wife]]
#:'''quotation''':
#:*"She was the cross her [[cuckolded]], incompatible husband had to bear, and he was - beneath those fantastic uniforms - the pathetic, '''uxorious''' human aggregate of love and good intentions, which, quite frankly, bored her most of the time." &mdash;''The Advertiser'', October 12, 1991

